<!-- Begin Title -->
<h1>Right Triangle</h1>
<!-- End Title -->
<hr class=3D"margin-t-1-8 margin-b-3-4">
<!-- Begin Total Content -->
<div class=3D"attachments text-align-r">
<a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/notebooks/PlaneGeometry/RightTrian=
gle.nb" download=3D"RightTriangle.nb"><img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram=
.com/images/entries/download-notebook-icon.png" width=3D"26" height=3D"27" =
alt=3D"DOWNLOAD Mathematica Notebook"><span>Download
 <span class=3D"display-i display-n__600">Wolfram&nbsp;</span>Notebook</spa=
n></a>
</div>
<!-- Begin Content -->
<div class=3D"entry-content">
<p>
A right triangle is <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Triangle.html"=
>triangle</a> with an <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Angle.html">=
angle</a> of <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Rig=
htTriangle/Inline1.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;ma=
x-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"28" height=3D"21" alt=3D"90 degrees"> (=
<img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/RightTriangle/In=
line2.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%"=
 border=3D"0" width=3D"29" height=3D"21" alt=3D"pi/2"> radians). The sides =
<img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/RightTriangle/In=
line3.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%"=
 border=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" alt=3D"a">, <img src=3D"https://mat=
hworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/RightTriangle/Inline4.svg" class=3D"inl=
ineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"=
9" height=3D"21" alt=3D"b">,
 and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/RightTriang=
le/Inline5.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:=
100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"8" height=3D"21" alt=3D"c">
 of such a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Triangle.html">triangle=
</a> satisfy the <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/PythagoreanTheore=
m.html">Pythagorean
 theorem</a>
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0" style=3D"padding-left: 50px">
<tbody><tr><td align=3D"left"><img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ima=
ges/equations/RightTriangle/NumberedEquation1.svg" class=3D"numberedequatio=
n" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"88" heigh=
t=3D"20" alt=3D" a^2+b^2=3Dc^2, "></td><td align=3D"right" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn1" class=3D"eqnum">
(1)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
where the largest side is conventionally denoted <img src=3D"https://mathwo=
rld.wolfram.com/images/equations/RightTriangle/Inline6.svg" class=3D"inline=
formula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"8" =
height=3D"21" alt=3D"c"> and is called the <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wol=
fram.com/Hypotenuse.html">hypotenuse</a>.
 The other two sides of lengths <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/i=
mages/equations/RightTriangle/Inline7.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D=
"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" alt=
=3D"a"> and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Righ=
tTriangle/Inline8.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max=
-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" alt=3D"b"> are called <=
a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Leg.html">legs</a>, or sometimes <a=
 href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Cathetus.html">catheti</a>.
</p>
<p>
The favorite A-level math exam question of the protagonist Christopher in t=
he novel <i><a href=3D"http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1400032717/re=
f=3Dnosim/ericstreasuretro">The
 Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-Time</a></i> asks for proof that =
a triangle
 with sides of the form <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/eq=
uations/RightTriangle/Inline9.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-hei=
ght:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"44" height=3D"21" alt=3D"n^2=
+1">,
 <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/RightTriangle/I=
nline10.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100=
